#compdef express
# ============================================================================
# express - Express application generator
#            scaffolder + the canonical Node
#            HTTP framework's reference CLI
#            (TypeScript/Node, MIT)
#
# Author : TJ Holowaychuk (original) +
#           Douglas Christopher Wilson (doug
#           wilson; long-time maintainer) +
#           Express team
#           (expressjs organization;
#           OpenJS Foundation hosted since
#           2019)
# Upstream: https://github.com/expressjs/generator
# npm pkg : express-generator
#
# `express` is the CLI scaffolder for new
# Express applications - generates a
# directory layout + boilerplate code for a
# new Express-based Node web app with
# optional template engine + CSS preprocessor
# choices. The CLI ships separately from the
# Express library itself but is the
# canonical entry point for new Express
# projects.
#
# Generated app structure:
#   - **bin/www** (the entry-point startup
#     script)
#   - **app.js** (Express app definition +
#     middleware setup)
#   - **routes/** (route handler modules)
#   - **views/** (template files for the
#     selected engine)
#   - **public/** (static assets)
#   - **package.json** (with Express +
#     selected engine deps configured)
#
# Distinguishing features vs alternatives
# (Yeoman generators + create-koa-app +
# nest CLI):
#   - **Official Express scaffolder**
#     (maintained by the expressjs
#     organization)
#   - **Multi-template engine support**
#     (Pug + EJS + Handlebars + Hogan +
#     Twig + Vash for view engines)
#   - **Multi-CSS-preprocessor support**
#     (LESS + Stylus + Compass + Sass +
#     plain CSS)
#   - **Minimal generated boilerplate**
#     (the canonical sparse Express app
#     starter; no extensive opinions
#     baked in like in NestJS or
#     fastify-cli)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Scaffolding new Express applications
#   - Bootstrapping tutorials + courses
#     (Express's official getting-started
#     workflow uses this CLI)
#   - Quick prototypes + proof-of-concept
#     Express services
#
# Usage:
#   express [options] [dir]
#
# View engine options:
#   -e, --ejs                      - add EJS
#                                     engine
#                                     support
#       --pug                      - add Pug
#                                     engine
#                                     support
#       --hbs                      - add
#                                     Handlebars
#                                     engine
#                                     support
#   -H, --hogan                    - add
#                                     Hogan.js
#                                     engine
#                                     support
#   -v, --view <engine>            - add
#                                     view
#                                     engine
#                                     support
#                                     (ejs +
#                                     hbs +
#                                     hjs +
#                                     pug +
#                                     twig +
#                                     vash;
#                                     default
#                                     pug)
#       --no-view                  - generate
#                                     app
#                                     without
#                                     view
#                                     engine
#                                     (API-
#                                     only
#                                     mode)
#
# CSS preprocessor options:
#   -c, --css <engine>             - add
#                                     stylesheet
#                                     engine
#                                     support
#                                     (less +
#                                     stylus
#                                     +
#                                     compass
#                                     + sass;
#                                     default
#                                     plain
#                                     CSS)
#
# Other options:
#       --git                      - add
#                                     .gitignore
#   -f, --force                    - force
#                                     generation
#                                     on
#                                     non-empty
#                                     directory
#   -h, --help                     - output
#                                     usage
#                                     information
#       --version                  - output
#                                     the
#                                     version
#                                     number
#
# Positional argument:
#   [dir]                          - directory
#                                     to
#                                     generate
#                                     the app
#                                     in
#                                     (default
#                                     current
#                                     directory)
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Default: Pug + plain CSS in current
#   # directory
#   express
#
#   # Specific directory + EJS templating
#   express my-app -e
#
#   # API-only mode (no view engine)
#   express --no-view my-api
#
#   # Custom view + CSS
#   express my-app -v hbs -c sass
#
#   # Force generation in non-empty dir +
#   # add .gitignore
#   express my-app -f --git
#
#   # Help
#   express --help
#
# After scaffolding:
#   cd my-app
#   npm install
#   npm start
#     # Server runs at http://localhost:3000
#
# The expressjs/express lane IS the canonical
# Node HTTP framework - this CLI is the
# official reference scaffolder by the
# expressjs organization (github.com/
# expressjs/generator).
#
# expressjs/express is the de-facto
# canonical Node HTTP framework:
#   - **THE original Node web framework**
#     (released 2010 by TJ Holowaychuk;
#     shaped the entire Node web ecosystem)
#   - **Sinatra-inspired API** (app.get +
#     app.post + app.use middleware
#     pattern; the canonical pattern that
#     spread to many other Node + non-Node
#     frameworks)
#   - **Middleware-first architecture**
#     (the (req, res, next) middleware
#     pattern is THE most-cloned API
#     design in web framework history)
#   - **Massive ecosystem** (~10,000+
#     express middleware packages on npm;
#     body-parser + cookie-parser +
#     compression + cors + helmet +
#     morgan + ...)
#   - **~32,000,000 weekly npm downloads**
#     (one of the highest-volume Node
#     libraries; pulled in by virtually
#     every Node web service)
#   - **65,000+ stars on github.com/
#     expressjs/express** (one of the
#     highest-star JavaScript repos)
#   - **OpenJS Foundation incubation
#     project** (since 2019; moved to
#     Foundation governance for long-term
#     stewardship)
#
# expressjs/express's distinguishing
# position vs Node HTTP framework
# alternatives:
#   - expressjs/express (Holowaychuk +
#     Wilson + Express team): canonical;
#     THE original; THIS AXIS
#   - koajs/koa (Holowaychuk + Koa team):
#     newer framework by the same
#     original author; async/await-first;
#     smaller ecosystem
#   - fastify (fastify/fastify): high-
